ðŸ‘‘ Super Admin Dashboard Overview A simple web-based admin dashboard to manage clubs, events, students, and admins. Built with plain HTML, CSS and JavaScript. Data is persisted in the browser using localStorage. Responsive design for desktop, tablet and mobile.

Features Club management: add / delete clubs Event management: add events linked to clubs Student management: add students with email and linked club Admin management: add admins linked to clubs Data persistence with localStorage Responsive layout with media queries No backend required (client-side only) Project structure Technologies HTML5 CSS3 (Flexbox, media queries, animations) JavaScript (Vanilla) â€” DOM manipulation, localStorage Quick start Clone or download the repository: Open super_admin.html in your browser, or use VS Code Live Server. 
No build or install required.

Usage (UI) Clubs: fill the club name (and description) â†’ click "Add Club". Clubs show in the clubs table. Events: enter event name, choose a club â†’ click "Add Event". Students: enter student name, email and choose a club â†’ click "Add Student". Admins: enter admin name and choose a club â†’ click "Add Admin". All changes are saved to localStorage and persist after refreshing the page.

Data saved in localStorage Keys used:

clubs â€” array of club objects events â€” array of event objects students â€” array of student objects (includes email) admins â€” array of admin objects idcounter â€” numeric id generator Example objects Club:

